# Project Structure Rules

## Root Directory
- `.cursor/` - Cursor rules and configuration
- `public/` - Static assets
- `src/` - Source code
- Configuration files at root level

## Source Directory (`src/`)

### Components (`src/components/`)
- Organized by feature or type
- Common components in `common/`
- Layout components in `layout/`
- Each component in its own directory with:
  - Main component file (`.jsx`)
  - Associated styles if needed
  - Tests (`.test.jsx`)

### Assets (`src/assets/`)
- Images, icons, fonts
- Organized by type
- Use descriptive names

### Hooks (`src/hooks/`)
- Custom React hooks
- One hook per file
- Prefix with `use`

### Services (`src/services/`)
- API calls
- External services integration
- Data fetching logic

### Styles (`src/styles/`)
- Global styles
- Theme configurations
- Tailwind custom styles

### Utils (`src/utils/`)
- Helper functions
- Constants
- Type definitions

## Entry Points
- `src/main.jsx` - Application entry
- `src/App.jsx` - Root component
- `src/index.css` - Global styles

## Configuration Files
- `vite.config.js` - Vite configuration
- `tailwind.config.js` - Tailwind configuration
- `postcss.config.js` - PostCSS configuration 